<item>
            <title>[LU-5070] Utility to change filesystem name</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-5070</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;It would be useful to have a utility to modify the name of an existing filesystem, though the filesystem would likely have to be unmounted from the clients/servers at the time.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This would require changes to:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;change labels of the backing filesystems (MDT/OST)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;change fsname and svname in mountdata (ldiskfs, or setting the equivalent ZFS dataset properties&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;rename the config log for this filesystem in /CONFIGS/
{fsname}
&lt;p&gt;-config, rewrite contents with new MDT/OST names on MGS, MDT, OST&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</description>
